default1.1
default              
defaultWith a membership of over 410,000 registered nurses, midwives, health visitors, nursing students, health care assistants and nurse cadets, 
defaultthe Royal College of Nursing (RCN) is the voice of nursing across the UK and the largest professional union of nursing staff in the world. RCN members work in a variety of hospital and community settings in the NHS and the independent sector. The RCN promo
defaulttes patient and nursing interests on a wide range of issues by working closely with the Government, the UK parliaments and other national and European political institutions, trade unions, professional bodies and voluntary organisations.
default&#xa0;
default1.2
default              
defaultThe RCN welco
defaultmes the opportunity to submit evidence to the
default Health Committee’s annual inquiry in to
default 
defaultpublic expenditure in the NHS. The RCN has responded to
default the elements of the terms of reference as
default posed by the Committee which it feels qualified to comment on. 
