defaultThe additional funding taken from the NHS budget - £1 billion a year by 2014 - is intended to be used for partnership working between the NHS and social care
default providers
default, to 
defaultallow for more people to be cared for in the community.  However, this funding is not ring-fenced and the RCN is concerned that this money is not being spent directly on this. The King’s Fund
default shares this concern
default and reports that t
defaulthe transfer of NHS resourc
defaultes is helping, but not always in the way intended – 
defaultto 
defaultprovid
defaulte
