default7.2
default              
defaultUsing the NHS budget to bail out social care goes against the Government's pledge to ring-fence and protect NHS spending. Without ensuring that these funds are spent on providing social care services, the NHS is still
default faced with filling the gaps in social care provision with all its associated costs and problems described above
default,
default but with £1 billion less funding.
